  "example_section_data": {
    "children": [
      {
        "type": "code",
        "value": "from scipy.cluster.hierarchy import ward, inconsistent, is_valid_im\nfrom scipy.spatial.distance import pdist"
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "value": "Given a data set ``X``, we can apply a clustering method to obtain a\nlinkage matrix ``Z``. `scipy.cluster.hierarchy.inconsistent` can\nbe also used to obtain the inconsistency matrix ``R`` associated to\nthis clustering process:"
      },
      {
        "type": "code",
        "value": "X = [[0, 0], [0, 1], [1, 0],\n     [0, 4], [0, 3], [1, 4],\n     [4, 0], [3, 0], [4, 1],\n     [4, 4], [3, 4], [4, 3]]"
      },
      {
        "type": "code",
        "value": "Z = ward(pdist(X))\nR = inconsistent(Z)\nZ"
      },
      {
        "type": "code",
        "value": "R"
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "value": "Now we can use `scipy.cluster.hierarchy.is_valid_im` to verify that\n``R`` is correct:"
      },
      {
        "type": "code",
        "value": "is_valid_im(R)"
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "value": "However, if ``R`` is wrongly constructed (e.g., one of the standard\ndeviations is set to a negative value), then the check will fail:"
      },
      {
        "type": "code",
        "value": "R[-1,1] = R[-1,1] * -1\nis_valid_im(R)"
      }
    ],
    "level": 0,
    "target": null,
